css:
@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);

@-moz-document domain("archiveofourown.org") {

/* ----------------------------------------------
Workskin is where you can change the grey
background color of the page. Simply delete this 
section to keep the grey or change #e4e3d5 to #ffffff
if you want the white background back. To make it 
black change the current color to #333333.
-------------------------------------------------*/

#main {
background-color: #E4E3D5 !important;
}

/* ----------------------------------------------
This is the information about the work at the top.
(It has things like rating, archive warning, etc.)
It also controls the top background behind logo, the
login button, etc. Background  Background color
controls the background. Color recommendations
include: grey (#E4E3D5), white (#ffffff), black
(#333333). Color controls the font color. If you're
using a black background, #eeeeee is recommended.
For white, dark black (#000000) or light black
(#333333) is recommended. Font-family is the font,
font-size is the size (go up in px to increase (ex.
15px) and down to decrease. To keep the default font
offered by AO3 simply remove the lines font-family
and font-size. It's currently arranged to resemble
fanfiction.net's font. Box-shadow removes the
annoying shadow around the box. Change its color
to the same color used in #main.
-------------------------------------------------*/

.wrapper {
background-color: #333333 !important;
color: #eeeeee !important;
font-family:  verdana !important;
font-size: 13px !important;
box-shadow: 0px 0px 0px #333333 !important;}
}

/* ----------------------------------------------
These are the link colors. I made them off white
(#eeeee) but any color will do. Off black (#333333)
is recommended for a white background.
-------------------------------------------------*/

.wrapper a {
color: #eeeeee !important; }

/* ----------------------------------------------
Workskin is the box that the story is inside of.
Width controls how far across it is. Size options
range from 0%-100%. Margin-top and padding were
added solely to keep the elements on the page from
ending up against one another after I edited it.
The border line is there incase you want the background
white (#ffffff) but it's relatively invisible and can
be removed if wanted. Background color controls the
background. Color recommendations include: grey
(#E4E3D5), white (#ffffff), black (#333333).
Color controls the font color. If you're using a 
black background, #eeeeee is recommended.
For white, dark black (#000000) or light black
(#333333) is recommended. Font-family is the font,
font-size is the size (go up in px to increase (ex.
15px) and down to decrease. To keep the default font
offered by AO3 simply remove the lines font-family
and font-size. It's currently arranged to resemble
fanfiction.net's font.
-------------------------------------------------*/

#workskin {
width: 70%;
margin-top: 40px !important;
border-bottom: 1px solid #D4D4D4;
padding: 0px 30px 30px 30px !important;
background-color: #333333 !important;
color: #eeeeee !important;
font-family:  verdana !important;
font-size: 13px !important;
}

/* ----------------------------------------------
This is the annoying shadow on the work title.
If using a dark background, keep the color #333333.
On a light background, use #ffffff.
-------------------------------------------------*/

h2 {
 text-shadow: 0px 0px 0px #333333 !important;}

/* ----------------------------------------------
This makes the background color of the login button
black if you changed the wrapper color. Simply
delete it if you prefer the white background.
-------------------------------------------------*/
#login {
background-color: #333333 !important;}

/* ----------------------------------------------
This makes the font color of all the buttons at
the top black.
-------------------------------------------------*/

.comments a, .share a, .download a {
color: #333333 !important; }

/* ----------------------------------------------
This changes all the feedback sections' fonts to
black. (Ex. the kudos, comment form, buttons for
comments, etc.) You can just take it all out if you
decide to use the white background.
-------------------------------------------------*/

#feedback {
color: #333333; }

#feedback {color: #333333 !important; }

#feedback a {color: #333333 !important; }

#feedback.kudos {color: #333333 !important; }

#feedback ul a {
color: #333333 !important; }

/* ----------------------------------------------
Happy customizing!
-------------------------------------------------*/
